<L>__{exterior highlands, glen gelder day}
<A>__{the stalking. everyone is now fanned out along the hillside, a ghillie to each gentleman, slowly and silently moving up the hill. disraeli stalks with brown, panting hard to keep up, eyes on his man, trying to make no sound. suddenly, brown stops. very slowly he rises. disraeli rides alongside and sees ... a huge stag staring majestically across the hillside. keeping his movements smooth and slow, brown brings up his rifle, cocks it and offers disraeli the kill. with a deferential gesture of the hands, disraeli declines. brown stares at him a split second, raises the rifle to his shoulder and fires.}
